tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within or very close to normal ranges. HbA1c and glucose indicate good glycemic control. Creatinine is slightly below the reference range but is not clinically significant in isolation. Renal, electrolyte, and metabolic parameters are unremarkable. No acute laboratory abnormalities detected. Recommend continued routine monitoring.
